rawReviews.text: Excellent customer service as soon as I contacted Express Rooter, beginning with Maddie, I received a text message informing me of the technician’s contact information that would be coming his name and a picture to show me who would be arriving. He took off his shoes before entering my home and he let me know that he had never found a tooth crown in anyone’s kitchen sink. He loosened the cv elbow pipe and poured its contents out in a plastic container and there was my crown. I was so excited because his cost was a lot cheaper than a new crown. He provided me with his business card and I will definitely use his services again and let everyone know how professional he was. He even pet my dog that was anxious and she calmed down barking. rawReviews.name: Professor Kellum
rawReviews.text: My wife called Express Rooter on the recommendation of our Foundation repair company.  She was told that they would give a free estimate on a small leak that we needed taken care of.  They came out this morning and went under the house.  When they came back out they told us that it would be 125 dollars.  The technician told us that it was just a loose connection that he hand tightened.  We were a little surprised by the 125 charge considering we had only called them out for a free estimate.  We talked to the manager over the phone and he said that it was a fair price because they had to come from Hartselle.  They also told us that if he hadn’t tightened the connection, it would have only been a 95 dollar service call charge.  No one told us anything about what was wrong or how it was fixed until we were handed the bill.  We contacted our foundation guy and asked him not to recommend Express Rooter to anyone in the Athens area, and I am refusing to recommend them for anyone.  Free estimates should not cost $125.

rawReviews.name: Michael Sims
rawReviews.text:
Promised an initial appointment to my uninhabited rental property: they showed up early, started working without full discussion and approval.  I only found out too late.  When they'd completed most of the digging and destruction, they called to let me know what they were doing.  The call was about a half hour before our agreed appointment.

When I arrived to meet them at the property, they described everything that needed to be done clearly.  They promised to be completed by the end of the day.

Though the guys worked hard, and it was STUPID hot out there, the job want done.  No problem, I thought.  We made an appointment for them to come back and finish it on Thursday.  I paid them for the whole job- even tipped the worker $50 on top of it.

Thursday came and went- not even a call from them.  Wish it had worked out differently.  Three stars for the hard work, two missing for not being there when they said they would... Either time.
rawReviews.title: Express Rooter Plumbing
